<p>Hurricane Melissa tore through the northern Caribbean this week, making landfall in Jamaica as a Category 5 storm and moving onward through Cuba and Haiti before threatening the Bahamas and Bermuda; the storm caused widespread structural damage and raised the death toll to multiple dozens as communities begin search, rescue and recovery . Emergency crews and governments are clearing roads, assessing infrastructure and sheltering displaced people while meteorologists warn Melissa will continue to produce dangerous winds and heavy rains as it tracks northward toward Bermuda and the U.S. Northeast .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/_7PVcGC51ah0COCt5kKWPh9j_YgzwIPEc0x3O6LcXf2cGcVYH9bHXvwERyY-iv7IzyCkx41nJuYOPFXYBXaFyNRjzXsORKH6HWWnSuNsf2mhPm_9HLa_GSTKG2Xc-0N3gNzVXB07TM9mcc3GXuYdxAhL3LdusdzvApQT3fLm9vo21pYCHDwnoSnOR78-fZKIR5K880hyoIdu0REWBK7qJI98Bh8ftjOQI-Qtp_i-KK4K78GBhw8ayQMc3WR0' alt='Residents stand on the wreckage of a house destroyed by Hurricane Melissa in Santa Cruz, Jamaica.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Country casualties: Officials reported dozens of deaths across the region, including at least 20 killed in a Haitian river overflow and multiple bodies recovered in Jamaica, with totals still rising as searches continue .</li><li>Displacement scale: Jamaica has tens of thousands sheltering and recovery teams describe communities isolated by downed trees and blocked roads as crews work to reach remote areas .</li><li>Infrastructure damage: The storm stripped roofs from houses, toppled utility poles and caused widespread power outages and flooding across eastern Cuba and southern Jamaica, complicating relief efforts .</li><li>Forecast hazards: Forecasters say Melissa will keep producing heavy rain and gusty winds as it moves past the Bahamas toward Bermuda and could fuel downpours over parts of the U.S. mid‑Atlantic and New England .</li><li>Relief mobilisation: The U.N. and humanitarian agencies are coordinating responses and the World Food Programme is preparing emergency assistance to support affected communities .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>United Nations coordinator in Jamaica: The devastation is tremendous and unprecedented, and Jamaica will need international support to recover. (<a href='https://www.theglobeandmail.com/world/video-devastation-from-hurricane-melissa-is-unprecedented-says-un/'>The Globe and Mail</a>)</li><li>Miguel Díaz-Canel (Cuban president): The cyclone had caused extensive damage. (<a href='https://english.elpais.com/climate/2025-10-30/hurricane-melissa-hits-cuba-the-night-lasted-too-long.html'>El País</a>)</li><li>Climate scientists / rapid analysis teams: Human-caused warming made a storm like Melissa more likely and increased its intensity. (<a href='https://www.ndtv.com/world-news/climate-change-made-hurricane-melissa-four-times-more-likely-study-9541688#publisher=newsstand'>NDTV</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/hurricane-melissa-destruction-jamaica-haiti-cuba/'>Hurricane Melissa&#x27;s deadly destruction leaves northern Caribbean reeling</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/haiti-jamaica-cuba-pick-pieces-after-melissas-destruction-127007361'>Haiti, Jamaica and Cuba pick up the pieces after Melissa&#x27;s destruction</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-10-30/in-pictures-hurricane-melissa-aftermath-in-cuba-jamaica-haiti/105953684'>Statellite images lay bare the extent of Hurricane Melissa&#x27;s damage</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2025/10/29/melissa-causes-havoc-in-jamaica-and-cuba'>Melissa causes havoc in Jamaica and Cuba</a> - mercopress.com</li><li><a href='https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2025/oct/29/hurricane-melissa-live-updates-strengthens-cuba-extensive-damage-parts-of-jamaica'>Hurricane Melissa death toll rises as storm wreaks destruction across Caribbean – as it happened</a> - theguardian.com</li><li